<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Seminole, Florida<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.60)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5383'>Mike "The Judge" Blumberg</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5383&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 27, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> This was the first LOTR constructed tournament in the Tampa Bay area. It was at Emerald City Comics in Seminole.<br>
<br>
I was playing a Nazgul shadow side and a machine gun fellowship with Gandalf for battling, condition removal, and the key to the deck Strength of Spirit. Basically everything that comes down is gunned down by Legolas and Aragorns aimed archery and anything with vitality enough to survive gets killed by swords or Servant of The Secret Fire. I will post this deck in a day or 2 as I am to tired tonight. Its really good.<br>
<br>
We had only 8 players because the tournament date had to change since I made it Feb 3rd which is Super Bowl and I am going so hard to run it from New Orleans. Some other guys were out of town this weekend to so we missed a few people.<br>
<br>
On to the games:<br>
<br>
Game 1 versus Brian Koepnick (90 card Gandalf/Moria deck)<br>
<br>
Brian is a new player and has discovered all the nuances yet of this game but he is learning quickly. he is a real nice guy to. I bid 3 and he bids 0 and I instruct him to go first. Telling someone to go first usually means Nazgul are on the way but he didnt catch that as he deployed Bilbo, Aragorn, and Butterburr and moved to Weatherhills where he met Attea and Cantea with 3 twilight in the pool. He does Gandlaf/Cantea first and play Mysterious Wizard upping the pool to five and I proceed to knock Ranger of The Norths pipeweed in the dirt. And then Gandalf takes another wound from Cantea. Nasty. Naturally he draws a bow and sword after. Doesnt that happen every time Aragorn gets killed? So he limps along for a couple of turns before succumbing at site 5 to like 3 fierce guys. Ouch.<br>
Full win 3 (3)<br>
<br>
Game 2 vs. Neal Razi Aragorn/Moria Swarm<br>
<br>
This was a great game as we both moved along slowly and cautiously. He outbid me and told me to go first. How rude.<br>
Nothing much happens until site 5 where I machine gun his swarm but deliver 3 blade tips to Aragorn and he dies at the next site. Frodo is all alone and dies at 7. My Aragorn took on 4 minions and some swords so the others could pass safely on. A very close good game.<br>
<br>
Game 3 vs Seth the Dwarven Chef Allison Dwarf pump/Moria<br>
<br>
How original another swarm deck. The word is out now...Mike is playing Nazgul...outbid him and tell him to go first. Swell.You dont realize how good dwarves are until they go pump pump pump die Cave Troll..ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha<br>
I wish they had higher vitality though. Anyway...I get 1st turn Aragorn, bow, sword, and saga!!! Amazing luck there. I slug and machine gun my way through swarm after swarm until site 8 when I do alot of damage to Gimli and Frodo with tips and breath and I walk to site 9 as he has run out of cards.<br>
<br>
Full win 3 (9)<br>
<br>
Game 4 vs Adam Martinez Dwarf pump/Moria swarm<br>
<br>
What do you thin th e meta is here? Moria swarm? Do you think? Out of 8 we had 6 swarms ,1 nazgul, and 1 Sauron. Groovy.<br>
<br>
Adam outbids me again 5-4 and says...I think you are playing Nazgul...you can go first. Like he didnt know. Little booger.<br>
He starts Gimil/Farin..deploys nothing moves to the marsh. I drop black breath and thats it. He wont double move.<br>
I move to the council courtyard and stop. he moves giving me 3 twilight. Wow. I drop 2 blade tips a morgul gates and Cantea. Insert sinister laugh here...Farin is overwhelmed and Gimli gets a new butthole right in the middle of his forehead and 2 tips and a breath and says...I lose.<br>
<br>
Full win 3 (12)<br>
<br>
So I win the tournament and go undefeated. yay!<br>
My fellowship goes through Moria minions like crap through a goose. I must have shut 40-50 Orcs today.<br>
<br>
1st Mike Blumberg<br>
2nd Neal Dredlox Razi<br>
3rd Adam Martinez<br>
4th Seth Allison<br>
5th Brian Koepnick<br>
6th Cynthia Hart<br>
7th Alice Martinez<br>
8th Sara Liles<br>
<br>
Props to me for running my first tournament of any kind and it went smoothly and I gave out some foils and packs and Im not even a Rider so it was my stuff. I just like people to have fun and get something cool. Its like Christmas.<br>
<br>
Props to the 7 others in the tournament. Thanks for coming. The next one should be bigger and better.<br>
<br>
Slops to the Rider for the St. Pete area. has not been seen except at the movie when it released and said he wouldnt be doing anything to promote the game or hold tournaments. What a loser. Must be nice to get handed 3 boxes, shirts, and other stuff for doing nothing.<br>
<br>
Till next time.<br>
<br>
Mike Blumberg <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3304&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
